-> Dependencies 
    numpy : sudo apt-get install python-numpy
    h5py  : sudo apt-get install python-h5py
    cv2   : http://docs.opencv.org/2.4/doc/tutorials/introduction/linux_install/linux_install.html 
            Also install python wrapper around cv2
Add cv2, h5py and numpy to PYTHON PATH

Enter mnist folder
-> data.py : generates train, val and test data
Run as : python data.py
This creates train, validation and test data folders with corresponding images.
Each image is of the form <image_label>_count.jpg, where count is a counter 
that runs from 0 to the number of images in that stage

-> create lmdb using this command : ../../../build/tools/convert_imageset ./data/ data/test.txt data/test_lmdb
Repeat this by replacing test_lmdb with train and valid

-> train model using this command    : ../../../build/tools/caffe train --solver=solver.prototxt

-> finetune model using this command : ../../../build/tools/caffe train --solver=solver.prototxt -weights=trained_models/lr_first_run.caffemodel
